Top 5 stations with the most starts (showing # of starts)¶

This notebook shows the top 5 stations with the maximum number of starts using an interactive map of NYC to see the various start stations and the number of starts from each.

#function to create a mp with the dataframe created above
def start_station_counts(s5):
    # generate a new map
    folium_map = folium.Map(location=[40.738, -73.98],zoom_start=13,tiles="CartoDB dark_matter",width='50%')
    # iterate through the rows in the dataframe and add a cicle marker
    for index, row in s5.iterrows():
        # popup message to show the station name and number of starts- pops up on click
        popup_text = "{}<br> number of starts:{}"
        popup_text = popup_text.format(row["start station name"],row["counts"])
        # radius of circle markers- bigger radius for higher counts
        radius = (row["counts"])/10000 
        
        # color of the marker
        if (row["counts"])>100000: #colors for the stations with the most starts
            color="#FFCE00" # yellow
            
        else:
            color="#0375B4" # blue
            
        # add marker to the map
        folium.CircleMarker(location=(row["start station latitude"],row["start station longitude"]),radius=radius,\
                            color=color,popup=popup_text,fill=True).add_to(folium_map)
        
    return folium_map

In the below map, the yellow circles are the top five stations with the maximum starts. Click on the circles to read the station name and the number of starts. The size of the circle is proportional to the number starts.
